    "body": "closes #7546 by adding the last two remaining overloads:\r\n\r\n- `ReduceByKey`\r\n- `TransformReduce`\r\n\r\nFor `DeviceReduce::TransformReduce` we maintain the deterministic guarantees (full determinism range) of `DeviceReduce::Reduce` as both go through RFA. The `transform`ation part happens before the reduction so the deterministic characteristics remain.\r\n\r\n`DeviceReduce::ReduceByKey`provides `run_to_run` determinism by construction. `gpu_to_gpu` determinism is not supported because the algorithm is based on a reduce-by-segment scan operating on `(value, flag)` pairs with inner decoupled lookback. Different tile sizes across architectures change where partial aggregates are combined relative to segment boundaries, making architecture-independent results infeasible.",
    "created_at": "2026-03-13T01:26:15Z",
    "updated_at": "2026-03-25T09:01:13Z",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-25T08:56:35Z",
